How food preservatives are harmful to people&#39;s health in Nigeria.
Some scientists have warned people to avoid eating food that has been used to prevent food spoilage because eating such food is harmful to human health.
The experts made this warning after the research they conducted on the quality of the food eaten in this country.
The results of the study show that there are some foods that have chemicals added to them to prevent them from rotting.
The research also shows that this ingredient is mostly used in beans, flour and dried fish that are sold to the public.
The substance is used because when a person sees it, he will want to buy it and use it.
And eating food that contains this ingredient causes cancer, kidney disease, heart attack and others.
The people of this country have been called to focus on avoiding the use of these types of food for their health.
Not to be forgotten, a food quality expert, Grace Olasumbo, has called on Nigerians to avoid eating fruits and vegetables that have been ground with Calcium Carbide.
Olasumbo explained that Calcium Carbide is the chemical most traders use to grind raw fruits and vegetables.
Research shows that impatience and greed are among the things that make businessmen use this substance because in one day it shows fruits.
Olasumbo explained that one thing that traders fail to understand is that the use of this chemical to display vegetables is very harmful to people&#39;s health.
Because of this, they get diseases including vomiting and diarrhea, eye disease, stomach ulcers, sore throat, mouth, liver and others.
