The Nigerian government has changed its position on student examinations.
The Nigerian government has changed its position on preventing children who are about to graduate from taking this year&#39;s exams, as a result of its new position of opening secondary schools from the 4th of next month to conduct the exams.
The spokesperson of the Ministry of Education of Nigeria, Ben Goong, said that the government has again approved the plan for the examination which will start from the 17th of August.
The official said that the opening of the schools on the 4th of tomorrow will give the students in the 3rd grade of high school the opportunity to prepare for two weeks before the exam.
This new position cancels the one taken by the Minister of Education, Adamu Adamu, who announced the suspension of the examination due to the increase in the number of people infected with the coronavirus in Nigeria.
During his explanation after assuming that position, the minister who said that the responsibility of the children of Nigerian students is his responsibility, he said that he will not refuse to cancel the exams completely this year to protect the health of the children.
